headlines.description: — Coby White scored a career-high 44 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Orlando Magic 125-123 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores career-high 44 points in the Bulls' 125-123 victory over the Magic

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 22 points and 16 assists, Onyeka Okongwu added 20 points and 13 rebounds and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Indiana Pacers 124-118 on Thursday night to open a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young has 22 points and 16 assists in the Hawks' 124-118 victory over the Pacers

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 35 points and seven rebounds and the Boston Celtics powered past the Philadelphia 76ers 123-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 35 to carry load for short-handed Celtics in 123-105 win over 76ers

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 40 points, with a turnaround heave from just inside halfcourt among his seven 3-pointers, and the Golden State Warriors climbed out of a 22-point hole to beat the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 40 points and the Warriors finish a 4-1 trip with a 121-119 victory over the Nets

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Amen Thompson had 21 points and 11 rebounds and the Houston Rockets had a dominating second half to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 109-97 on Thursday night to open a home-and-home set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets take over after halftime in a 109-97 road victory over Pelicans

events.name: New York Knicks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 32 points, LeBron James added 31 and the Los Angeles Lakers extended their winning streak to eight games by overcoming a double-digit deficit in the fourth quarter and defeating the New York Knicks 113-109 in overtime Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic and James propel Lakers to 113-109 overtime victory over Knicks for 8th straight win
